  "summary": "Lynn Marchmont receives a series of phone calls. First, her Aunt Kathy calls from a public booth, sounding weak and claiming to have made a mess of a meeting at a college. Kathy mentions her phone is broken. Following this, an unidentified caller seeking Lynn briefly connects before the line fails. Shortly after, David calls Lynn from London with an air of urgency and excitement. He reveals that his previous claims of wanting to leave the Vale of Worms were a pretense to hide his desire to stay. However, he now declares his intention to leave Britain entirely. David tells Lynn that they have no future together, calls himself a scoundrel, and suggests she marry Rolly instead before abruptly ending the call with a curse.\n\nMeanwhile, at a location called Stagg, a maid named Gladys discovers the body of a guest, Enoch Yaton, in Room 5. Yaton is lying face down with a smashed head. Gladys alerts Beatrice Lippincott and Dr. Lionel Crowd. Upon inspecting the body, Dr. Crowd instructs Beatrice to call the police, while warning Gladys against speculating that the death is a murder to avoid libel. Superintendent Spence arrives and takes a statement from Beatrice regarding a conversation she overheard. Although Beatrice hopes the death might be a suicide, Spence notes that the victim was struck on the back of the head with steel fire tongs. Spence reviews Beatrice's testimony, noting that while it contains some excitement-driven embellishments, the core of her account is sinister and intriguing.",
